The paper deals with a low-complexity detection algorithm for MIMO-NOMA systems, which involves information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), signal processing (cs.SI), multimedia (cs.MM), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper discusses the convergence analysis of the algorithm, which is a fundamental problem in information theory and signal processing. Therefore, cs.IT and cs.SI are the most likely categories. The paper also considers the cases where $N_u>N_r$, which is related to the design of wireless networks and communication protocols, and hence, cs.NI is also a likely category. The paper uses the large-scale property of the MIMO-NOMA to simplify the convergence analysis, which is a common technique in machine learning and optimization, and hence, cs.LG is also a likely category. Finally, the paper provides numerical results to verify the theoretical results, which is related to multimedia applications, and hence, cs.MM is also a likely category.
